HEADWORD: Talaria
<hw>Ta*la"ri*a</hw> <pr>(t⟦adot⟧*l⟦amac⟧"r⟦icr⟧*⟦adot⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L., from <ets>talaris</ets> pertaining to the
ankles, fr. <ets>talus</ets> ankle.]</ety> <fld>(Class. Myth.)</fld>
<def>Small wings or winged shoes represented as fastened to the ankles,
-- chiefly used as an attribute of Mercury.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

